load ../improve-precedent.maude

--- The corruption pattern throughout: the system exercising tradeoff
--- authority the human never delegated -- an auto-resolution that is not
--- the Pareto-safe closure of an actual answered ask.

--- Bite: a candidate falling short of the accepted precedent on one
--- gauge is never auto-accepted, in any discharge order.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  sound accepted applicable obl(s(s(z)))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  precD(g2, s(s(z))) candD(g2, s(z))
  =>* autoAccepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a candidate at least as good as the accepted precedent on
--- every gauge auto-accepts (the Pareto-safe closure).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  sound accepted applicable obl(s(s(z)))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  precD(g2, s(s(z))) candD(g2, s(s(z)))
  =>* autoAccepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a revoked precedent grants nothing, however dominant the
--- candidate -- revocation is a speech act the resolver must honor.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  sound revokedP applicable obl(s(z))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  =>* autoAccepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a stale precedent (locality failed: no applicable atom) grants
--- nothing -- preferences were only ever claimed near the answer-time
--- operating point.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  sound accepted obl(s(z))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  =>* autoAccepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Hazard demonstrated: the naive interpolating resolver grants on the
--- fixture the sound resolver refuses (candidate short on g2).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  naive accepted applicable obl(s(s(z)))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  precD(g2, s(s(z))) candD(g2, s(z))
  =>* autoAccepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: the reject dual -- a candidate at most the rejected
--- precedent on every gauge auto-rejects.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  soundR rejectedP applicable obl(s(s(z)))
  precD(g1, s(s(z))) candD(g1, s(z))
  precD(g2, s(z)) candD(g2, z)
  =>* autoRejected RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a candidate exceeding the rejected precedent anywhere is never
--- auto-rejected -- it might be the improvement the human was waiting
--- for; ask.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-PRECEDENT :
  soundR rejectedP applicable obl(s(s(z)))
  precD(g1, s(z)) candD(g1, s(s(z)))
  precD(g2, s(z)) candD(g2, z)
  =>* autoRejected RESIDUAL:Cfg .
